Description. Fully grown adult shells are rather small (
Table 2
), rarely reaching more than 2 mm , longer than wide; strongly ventribiconvex (Pl. 1 , Fig. 1 d–e). The relationships between ratios length/width (L/W) and width, length of dorsal valve/width (LDV/W) and width, thickness/width (T/W) and width, and length of hinge line/width (WH/W) and width are illustrated in Text-Fig. 2 . The shell is endopunctate, with large punctae. The anterior commissure is rectimarginate (Pl. 1 , Fig. 1 e). The lateral commissure is straight. The hinge line is straight and its length represents 50 to 75 % of the maximum width of the shell (
Table 2
).
